  <Subject Subject_ID="300207459">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300205019</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>sound signaling devices [300205019], sound devices by function [300205016], sound devices (equipment) [300387677], Sound Devices (hierarchy name) [300041619], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Devices for producing sounds, consisting essentially of a disk pierced with holes arranged in a circle, rotated over a stream of compressed air, steam, or fluid, so that the stream is alternately interrupted and allowed to pass; their uses include giving signals or warnings and producing musical tones.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046682/Random House Dictionary of the English Language (1987)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Artefactos que producen sonidos, consistentes esencialmente en un disco perforado con agujeros organizados en círculo que se hace rotar sobre una corriente de aire comprimido, vapor o fluído de manera que la corriente es alternativamente interrumpida y autorizada a pasar; sus usos incluyen dar señales o alarmas y producir tonalidades musicales.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Apparaten voor het produceren van waarschuwingssignalen, ook voor het maken van muziek bestaande uit een cirkelvormig geperforeerde schijf, draaibaar boven een stroom van samengeperste lucht, stoom of vloeistof.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052381/Van Dale Engels-Nederlands (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gerät zur Erzeugung von Tönen, das hauptsächlich aus einer Scheibe mit eingestanzten Löchern in kreisförmiger Anordnung besteht. Die Scheibe dreht sich über einem Strom von Druckluft, Dampf oder Flüssigkeit, sodass der Strom abwechselnd unterbrochen oder durchgelassen wird; zur Nutzung des Gerätes zählt die Signalgebung oder Warnung und Erzeugung von Musikklängen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
